---
title: Healthcare Patient Portal
projectContext: A regional healthcare network with 14 clinics needed to replace their outdated patient portal with a modern, accessible platform. The existing system had poor adoption rates — less than 18% of patients used it — and the support team was fielding hundreds of calls per week for tasks that should have been self-service.
problem: The legacy portal was built in 2014 and hadn't kept pace with patient expectations or regulatory requirements. It failed WCAG 2.1 accessibility audits, didn't work on mobile devices, and required patients to remember a separate username and password. Appointment scheduling required calling the clinic directly because the portal's booking flow was too confusing to complete.
solution: Designed and built a new patient portal with a mobile-first approach, single sign-on via the patient's existing email, and a streamlined appointment booking flow that reduced the steps from 11 to 4. Implemented full WCAG 2.1 AA compliance and integrated directly with the clinic's Epic EHR system for real-time appointment and records access.
outcome: Patient portal adoption increased from 18% to 61% within six months of launch. Support call volume for self-service tasks dropped by 67%. Patient satisfaction scores for digital interactions improved by 28 points on the clinic's quarterly survey. The portal handled over 40,000 appointment bookings in its first year without a single critical incident.
